Weighted Average Cost Of Capital formula;
{eq}\text{WACC} = \displaystyle \text{Weight}_{equity} \times Cost_{equity} + \text{Weight}_{debt} \times Cost_{debt} \times (1 - \text{Tax rate}) {/eq}
It is obvious that a lower tax rate will raise the after-tax cost of debt. Thus, the firm's WACC will increase if all other inputs are constant.
